<dl id="n54148e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54148e">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54148e"> 148(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> paddyplanters / walk bowed <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54148e"><li>FW 25.19 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n54148e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n54148e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54148e">MS BL 47476b-474</ms> </li><li>JJA 50:278 <a name="ad8" href="../../FF/fdra/ada.htm#ad8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad8.htm#n54148e">Draft: I.1&sect;1.8</a>/2.8</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Quand les Nagas descendent de la colline o&ugrave; ils ont travaill&eacute; &agrave; leur rizi&egrave;re, <mark>le dos courb&eacute; comme si leurs &eacute;paules fl&eacute;chissaient sous la charge du paddy</mark>, cette mimique signifie : &laquo;Puisse la r&eacute;colte &ecirc;tre tellement abondante que nous ayons grand&apos;peine &agrave; la transporter en bas !&raquo; Le souhait s&apos;exprime non par des paroles, mais par la pr&eacute;figuration de l&apos;effort qui sera n&eacute;cessaire apr&egrave;s la moisson. Cette mimique est, si l&apos;on peut dire, un indicatif en acte. Il tient la place d&apos;un optatif-jussif, qui oblige le fait qu&apos;il &eacute;nonce &agrave; se r&eacute;aliser. Bref, cette mimique est une formule en action. <br><font color="green">[When the Nagas descend from the hill where they worked in their rice field, their backs bent as if their shoulders were bending under the load of the paddy, this expression means: "May the harvest be so abundant that we have great difficulty transporting it downstairs! The wish is expressed not in words, but in foreshadowing the effort that will be required after the harvest. This mimicry is, so to speak, an indicative in action. It takes the place of an opt-jussive, which forces the fact that it states to come true. In short, this expression is a formula in action.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 286</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Paddy fields (rice). </mm> </dd></dl>
